# React Data Fetching Patterns -- {{PROJECT_NAME}}

> Standard hook patterns for data fetching, mutations, and caching.
> All hooks follow a consistent API envelope unwrap pattern.

---

## API Envelope

The backend wraps all responses in a standard envelope. **Always unwrap it.**

```typescript
// Backend response shape
interface ApiResponse<T> {
  {{API_ENVELOPE_DATA_KEY}}: T;
  {{API_ENVELOPE_META_KEY}}?: { total: number; page: number; pageSize: number };
  {{API_ENVELOPE_MESSAGE_KEY}}?: string;
}

// CORRECT: unwrap the envelope
const items = response.{{API_ENVELOPE_DATA_KEY}};

// WRONG: use response directly (will cause "undefined" bugs)
const items = response;
```

