## Common Pitfalls

| Pitfall | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Not unwrapping the API envelope | Always access `response.{{API_ENVELOPE_DATA_KEY}}` |
| Missing `enabled` flag on detail hooks | Add `enabled: !!id` to prevent fetching with undefined |
| Forgetting to invalidate after mutations | Always invalidate related query keys in `onSuccess` |
| Unstable query key references | Use primitive values in keys, not objects that change identity |
| Missing error handling in UI | Wrap with `ErrorBoundary` or check `isError` from the hook |
| Fetching on every render | Ensure params are stable (useMemo/useState, not inline objects) |
